subject: The Haiku Influence on Modern Nature Poetry (1910s–1920s)
permalink: /The Haiku Influence on Modern Nature Poetry (1910s–1920s)/HD/HD - They Are Gone
---

They are gone, the soft-lit petals
Crushed into one shape,
Too delicate to bear, and yet the air,
Still warm, exudes such fragrance—I must breathe
The very explosion of green color,
The gentle sound of petals falling.

- HD
